cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.CR, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the challenges and solutions for installing, running, and maintaining large Linux clusters at CERN. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper mentions the need for shared interactive and batch services that can adapt to meet the diverse and changing requirements of users. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is another possible category as the paper discusses the tools and processes implemented for system installation, configuration, and monitoring. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is mentioned briefly in the paper as one of the challenges faced in managing large clusters. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also possible as the paper discusses the development and tuning introduced on LSF based systems to maximize responsiveness to users and overall system utilization.
